The paper deals with transmission schemes in wireless relay networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The proposed schemes involve linear transformations and distributed space-time coding, which are common techniques in the signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) fields. Finally, the paper also discusses the complexity of the proposed schemes, which is a topic of interest in the computer communications (cs.COM) community.
